Package: wtftools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python3, python3-psutil
Recommends: systemd, cron
Description: One command to see what is going on with your Linux server right now
 wtftools provides a single command "wtf" that runs 15+ diagnostic checks in
 parallel and reports them as a green/yellow/red checklist. Includes:
  * wtf info     - quick host snapshot (uptime, load, memory, disks, top procs)
  * wtf audit    - OK/WARN/FAIL audit of the most common SRE checkpoints
  * wtf crontab  - full crontab validator (absorbs the checkcrontab tool)
 .
 The tool is stdlib-only at its core and degrades gracefully when systemctl or
 journalctl are absent. Designed for SREs and solo developers who want a
 diagnosis, not yet another metrics dashboard.
